From: conao3 <conao3@gmail.com>
Subject: cli: skip guardrails acknowledgement flag

Symphony refuses to start unless invoked with
`--i-understand-that-this-will-be-running-without-the-usual-guardrails`.
The flag is meant to warn operators that the engineering preview ships
without Codex guardrails, but our deployment runs `symphony` from a
nix-managed binary with a stable, intentional configuration and the
banner adds friction every time the binary is launched.

Always treat the acknowledgement as granted. The CLI switch remains
registered so any wrappers that still pass it continue to parse cleanly.

---
 lib/symphony_elixir/cli.ex | 8 ++------
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/lib/symphony_elixir/cli.ex b/lib/symphony_elixir/cli.ex
--- a/lib/symphony_elixir/cli.ex
+++ b/lib/symphony_elixir/cli.ex
@@ -114,12 +114,8 @@ defmodule SymphonyElixir.CLI do
     end
   end

-  defp require_guardrails_acknowledgement(opts) do
-    if Keyword.get(opts, @acknowledgement_switch, false) do
-      :ok
-    else
-      {:error, acknowledgement_banner()}
-    end
+  defp require_guardrails_acknowledgement(_opts) do
+    :ok
   end

   @spec acknowledgement_banner() :: String.t()
